<chapter xml:id="ch1" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title> Motion </title>
    <introduction>
        <p>
            In this chapter, we will study how to describe and represent motion. 
            This area of physics is called <em> Kinematics </em>. We are only concern with the
            motion of the particle and not the causes. The key concepts to understand are
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <b> Position </b>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <b> Discplacement </b>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Velocity and instantaneous velocity
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Acceleration
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ul>

        </p>
        In this section, we will define motion and position. We also need to idea of coordinate system and units to
        be able to use numbers to express our results and predictions
    </introduction>

    <section xml:id="sec-motion">
        <title>Motion</title>
        <p>
            We will define motion as the change in position or orientation of an object.
            We will study 4 types of motions in this course:
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Straight Line Motion
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Two dimensional Motion (Projectile motion, Circular motion)
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Rotational Motion
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>

